2752
03:30:53,838 --> 03:30:55,899
So now I'm going to speak quickly as a school committee member.

2753
03:30:55,919 --> 03:30:58,341
And I have a few thoughts about what I've heard here tonight.

2754
03:31:00,280 --> 03:31:05,462
I find it, first of all, I just want to find it amusing that anybody thinks a three and a half hour meeting is even remotely long.

2755
03:31:05,862 --> 03:31:08,384
School committee meetings are eight hours on a regular basis.

2756
03:31:08,604 --> 03:31:10,184
So I just kind of giggle at that.

2757
03:31:10,204 --> 03:31:11,265
So I'm kind of light.

2758
03:31:12,606 --> 03:31:17,848
But anyways, when I took office, I had heard from several members of the council,

2759
03:31:18,964 --> 03:31:22,525
The school committee shouldn't be in the city council's pool and we shouldn't be in yours.

2760
03:31:22,966 --> 03:31:24,786
And I fully support that.

2761
03:31:25,287 --> 03:31:30,909
I agree both bodies have enough work to do without also trying to be involved in each other's work.

2762
03:31:32,430 --> 03:31:35,571
If you look at the budgets for the last decade, you'll see an org chart.

2763
03:31:36,131 --> 03:31:39,312
The mayor, the city council and the school committee are all on the same level.

2764
03:31:39,573 --> 03:31:40,693
We don't report to each other.

2765
03:31:42,394 --> 03:31:45,295
So why am I speaking then at a city council meeting?

2766
03:31:46,538 --> 03:31:53,441
because I've heard several times tonight about the school committee meeting from counselors either directly or indirectly.

2767
03:31:54,461 --> 03:31:56,502
So here's what I have to say on some of those comments.

2768
03:31:57,802 --> 03:32:02,844
The school committee does not have taxation authority or the ability to decide how much money we are given.

2769
03:32:03,284 --> 03:32:05,325
That is the job of the city council and the mayor.

2770
03:32:06,403 --> 03:32:11,427
So when you talk about the layoffs in the school department, I take offense- For your information, Mr. President.

2771
03:32:11,487 --> 03:32:13,029
For your information, Councilor Marks.

2772
03:32:13,549 --> 03:32:19,974
Just for the edification of the gentlemen, the city council does not decide the money that's given to the school committee.

2773
03:32:20,715 --> 03:32:24,178
Just to, you know, if we're gonna talk facts, let's talk facts.

2774
03:32:25,479 --> 03:32:27,601
Thank you, so I won't respond to that.

2775
03:32:29,022 --> 03:32:30,203
Because there is none, Paul.

2776
03:32:31,412 --> 03:32:32,974
That's right, you don't have to approve our budget.

2777
03:32:33,295 --> 03:32:33,695
That's right.

2778
03:32:34,376 --> 03:32:36,239
You don't approve- That's not what you said, Paul.

2779
03:32:36,479 --> 03:32:38,221
Let's get the facts, what you're saying, Paul.

2780
03:32:38,482 --> 03:32:39,543
Facts matter, Paul.

2781
03:32:39,784 --> 03:32:43,369
You can't just speak and not- One at a time.

2782
03:32:43,489 --> 03:32:44,811
Councilor Marks has the floor.

2783
03:32:44,951 --> 03:32:46,132
Councilor Marks has the floor.

2784
03:32:46,913 --> 03:32:49,994
Mr. President, facts speak for themselves, Mr. President.

2785
03:32:50,014 --> 03:32:54,435
The gentleman can't accept that that is not the process, Mr. President.

2786
03:32:54,715 --> 03:32:58,416
And he's been saying a lot of things that aren't processed over the last couple of weeks.

2787
03:32:58,876 --> 03:33:01,057
He should know what the process is, Mr. President.

2788
03:33:01,377 --> 03:33:01,977
You are correct.

2789
03:33:05,138 --> 03:33:07,838
I take offense and disagree that we are laying anyone off.

2790
03:33:08,018 --> 03:33:09,599
The city is laying staff off.

2791
03:33:10,079 --> 03:33:14,020
Literally every school committee member, and I would suggest everyone that's ever served,

2792
03:33:14,625 --> 03:33:16,686
would add dozens of personnel every year.

2793
03:33:16,967 --> 03:33:20,049
So pinning this on the school committee is unacceptable, in my opinion.

2794
03:33:22,130 --> 03:33:29,035
Next, I would like to discuss the renaming of the Columbus School directly and the assertion that this has divided this community.

2795
03:33:29,435 --> 03:33:30,856
I greatly appreciate the quote.

2796
03:33:31,677 --> 03:33:42,745
Any time anyone says, we've never been more divided about a country that was legally segregated within many of its current citizens' lifetimes, I guess at least

2797
03:33:43,954 --> 03:33:46,175
They're making it clear who their we is.

2798
03:33:46,935 --> 03:33:49,296
Medford was redlining not very long ago.

2799
03:33:49,897 --> 03:33:55,459
The boundaries of neighborhoods were carefully drawn to make sure as few black kids as possible would go to school with white kids.

2800
03:33:55,819 --> 03:33:58,080
And that is not before I was born.

2801
03:33:59,221 --> 03:34:02,242
Medford has not been united, never has been.

2802
03:34:03,543 --> 03:34:12,727
And I think that using that Medford as this united thing, it's just, it's crap, frankly, pardon my language.

2803
03:34:16,448 --> 03:34:21,190
I also want to say that I look forward to responding to any open meeting law violations that are filed against me.

2804
03:34:21,770 --> 03:34:29,052
I have attended open meeting law trainings three years in a row as a school committee member during the school committee associations trainings.

2805
03:34:29,633 --> 03:34:31,553
And I'm pretty confident on my interpretation.

2806
03:34:32,614 --> 03:34:38,796
If you ask my colleagues on the school committee, they will all tell you that I'm obsessed with the open meeting law and following the process.

2807
03:34:39,736 --> 03:34:44,878
I've received a call today from a senior member asking me a question about open meeting law.

2808
03:34:46,169 --> 03:35:05,590
to have this body say anything about transparency when it was normal, if not on every meeting, if it was normal, if not on every meeting for up to 75 years, according to one of the members during their debate on this, that they would just add items to the agenda when they showed up.

2809
03:35:06,523 --> 03:35:13,887
both in violation of the open meeting law and the opposite of transparency and access that I've heard a few things about tonight.

2810
03:35:14,368 --> 03:35:18,130
So you just show up, add stuff to the agenda, talk about it, and the public hasn't got a clue.

2811
03:35:19,470 --> 03:35:28,636
After I filed my open meeting law violation, this body had a meeting to discuss the fact that the city solicitor had agreed that you all cannot do that.

2812
03:35:29,756 --> 03:35:35,720
And finally, apparently after 75 years, you don't just add stuff to the agenda when you walk in the room or show up to your meetings.

2813
03:35:38,980 --> 03:35:41,361
I recommend that folks go back and look at that meeting.

2814
03:35:41,401 --> 03:35:42,321
It was earlier this year.

2815
03:35:42,721 --> 03:35:50,983
There were some members that were shocked, utterly shocked, and had intense disagreement that this opinion from the city solicitor was accurate.

2816
03:35:52,483 --> 03:35:56,844
So I will not accept any critiques on transparency, access, or process from this body.

2817
03:35:58,005 --> 03:35:58,345
Thank you.

2818
03:36:00,005 --> 03:36:00,365
Thank you.

2819
03:36:03,026 --> 03:36:03,386
Thank you.

