03:36:45,509 --> 03:36:47,050
Thank you, President Falco.

2833
03:36:47,730 --> 03:36:49,751
I know it's been a long evening for all.

2834
03:36:50,191 --> 03:36:53,893
Paul Camuso, 114 Lincoln Road here in Medford.

2835
03:36:54,273 --> 03:36:58,015
But thank you for calling on me, Mr. President Falco.

2836
03:36:59,015 --> 03:37:06,879
I speak from my experience as a member of the school committee and as a city councilor for about 16 years here in our community.

2837
03:37:08,360 --> 03:37:10,921
First of all, the budget that we received, I want to thank the mayor.

2838
03:37:11,921 --> 03:37:12,542
Read it online.

2839
03:37:13,562 --> 03:37:19,267
It's got a lot of information, a total overhaul of budgets of years past.

2840
03:37:19,867 --> 03:37:23,491
And I'm glad that it was presented in the format that it was.

2841
03:37:23,551 --> 03:37:26,493
I think it's a great collaboration from all the department heads.

2842
03:37:27,274 --> 03:37:29,816
The narratives were great and the charts and things of that nature.

2843
03:37:31,177 --> 03:37:40,185
But as far as the discussion that's going on regarding meeting in Zoom and meeting in the council chambers,

2844
03:37:41,040 --> 03:37:46,544
I absolutely understand that there is a lot of value in meeting at the council chambers.

2845
03:37:47,445 --> 03:37:56,672
You know, yeah, when you have to look people in the eye on tough debates and things of that nature, and quite honestly, after watching this meeting,

2846
03:37:57,159 --> 03:38:02,981
and some other meetings that are on Zoom, the decorum, the Robert's Rules of Order are in place for a reason.

2847
03:38:03,341 --> 03:38:13,405
And it's a lot easier to keep an orderly meeting, I think, if you're at a public meeting rather than on Zoom, just because the technology is a little bit different.

2848
03:38:14,385 --> 03:38:18,526
But like I said, I do not envy any of you guys during this COVID time.

2849
03:38:19,107 --> 03:38:28,370
This city has stepped up amazingly, the city council, the mayor's office, the school department, everybody, to meet the needs of the people in our community with this COVID-19.

2850
03:38:28,750 --> 03:38:31,591
It's unprecedented, as we all know.

2851
03:38:32,071 --> 03:38:38,933
And I think that somewhere along the line, and I really got to credit the entire council tonight

2852
03:38:39,415 --> 03:38:40,416
for the motion that was made.

2853
03:38:40,436 --> 03:38:43,280
I believe it's basically for like a mediation with the mayor.

2854
03:38:43,320 --> 03:38:50,669
I don't know if that's the correct word to use, but Marianne O'Connor, who I've had the privilege of knowing over the years, she is a consummate professional.

2855
03:38:51,142 --> 03:38:55,104
and as well as the members of the school committee, the council, the mayor's office.

2856
03:38:55,764 --> 03:38:58,785
If there's a way to do a hybrid model, I think it would be the best.

2857
03:38:59,906 --> 03:39:09,550
Just because of the fact, like you said, people can have both, you can come down there if your health allows you to, and you can also participate on Zoom.

2858
03:39:09,810 --> 03:39:14,311
The one good thing that I am encouraged by this evening is the participation, but

2859
03:39:15,712 --> 03:39:24,095
The name calling and stuff that was allowed to happen tonight on all sides of this issue, it's not Medford that we can be proud of, to be quite frank.

2860
03:39:24,535 --> 03:39:29,616
We should all be working together to move Medford forward in a way that we all love Medford.

2861
03:39:29,917 --> 03:39:33,778
Whether you've been here for a hundred years or you've been here for a hundred days, it doesn't matter.

2862
03:39:33,978 --> 03:39:37,439
You moved here because you like something in this community and it can always be better.

2863
03:39:38,052 --> 03:39:38,952
It can always be better.

2864
03:39:40,193 --> 03:39:49,938
I suggest, like I said, I hope tomorrow Vice President Carviello, President Falco, with the mayor and other people can sit down and let cooler heads prevail.

2865
03:39:50,318 --> 03:39:59,543
One thing that has been frustrating on Zoom, just when I've watched it, is sometimes they have to call the roll three, four, five times to find out how people are voting and stuff.

2866
03:40:00,103 --> 03:40:02,084
The technology is iffy.

2867
03:40:02,904 --> 03:40:03,405
I understand

2868
03:40:04,714 --> 03:40:09,061
I understand that it's a good tool, but at the same token, it's something that can...

2869
03:40:10,413 --> 03:40:13,936
whether it's a slow internet connection on a specific night or something.

2870
03:40:14,416 --> 03:40:26,166
Um, it does, does can get challenging, you know, but, uh, for our community, for the Medford that we all love, let cooler heads prevail and, uh, let's get the budget and do it, uh, do it the right way.

2871
03:40:26,426 --> 03:40:30,109
And I, and I just would like to, uh, hopefully it's a hybrid if we can do it in a safe manner.

2872
03:40:30,630 --> 03:40:39,557
And, uh, as far as both sides of the issue, I understand, I understand both sides of the issue, but I cannot state loud enough the value of

2873
03:40:40,135 --> 03:40:43,698
having a meeting with people once it's safe to do so.

2874
03:40:44,359 --> 03:40:53,808
So I would encourage you, would strongly encourage you guys to try to do some sort of hybrid model, because this might be another year before we're out of the woods with COVID.

2875
03:40:55,609 --> 03:40:59,033
The numbers are going up and down as we see all over the country right now.

2876
03:40:59,413 --> 03:41:00,474
We don't know where we're gonna be.

2877
03:41:01,495 --> 03:41:04,378
The city has done a tremendous job getting the,

2878
03:41:05,590 --> 03:41:09,891
the PPE out there and things of that nature, working with the partners in federal and state government.

2879
03:41:10,271 --> 03:41:11,832
But we don't know where we're going down the road.

2880
03:41:12,512 --> 03:41:15,073
So people's individual needs can be met.

2881
03:41:15,273 --> 03:41:22,054
And I've always been a big person for meeting the individual needs of constituents as we all are when we're elected officials.

2882
03:41:22,434 --> 03:41:32,057
But if we have both, I think it would be the best because I think the decorum, most importantly, would be brought back to a place that we can all be proud of.

2883
03:41:33,325 --> 03:41:39,891
in a setting less virtual, but also virtual for the people that do have health needs that may need it.

2884
03:41:40,171 --> 03:41:41,732
So that's all I have tonight.

2885
03:41:42,113 --> 03:41:44,295
And once again, just good luck with this budget.

2886
03:41:44,675 --> 03:41:45,916
Budget time is never easy.

2887
